HEADWORD: Piacle
<hw>Pi"a*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>piaculum</ets> a propitiatory sacrifice, that which requires
expiation, a wicked action, fr. <ets>piare</ets> to appease, to expiate,
<ets>pius</ets> pious.]</ety> <def>A heinous offense which requires
expiation.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Howell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

